{
  "texts": [
    "One such \"cathartic object\" designed by Luria is a cushion that vibrates in reaction to being poked by a sharp tool.",
    "The more tools you put into the cushion, the more it vibrates until it shakes so violently that the tools fall out.",
    "You can repeat the process as much as desired.",
    "The objects presented by Luria as potential agents of negativeemotion relief are simply moving, responsive objects at this stage.",
    "However, Luria proposes the use of more humanlike agents, such as social robots, as cathartic objects."
  ]
}